<h2>The Life of our Stars</h2>

<p>The tiny specks of matter drew together, forming giant dust clouds. These grew so massive that its own mass caused it to condense into a baby star, a protostar.
</p>

<p>And in the heart of these stars, was made the oxygen that exists in the air that we breathe, as well as the carbon that makes us and all life on Earth.
</p>

<p>In fact, these stars would make almost all of the elements we see around us now, either during their lives or at the end of it.
</p>

<p>If the star was particularly massive then at the end of its life, when it has made all it can and become as large as possible…bang! It explodes, creating new elements and flooding the area with stardust, which eventually comes together to form planets, like ours, and everything on it.
</p>

